{"tid":1929200,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"[美國JJ] SF 三潘市封城 唔俾岀街","createTime":"2020-03-16T21:40:06.000Z","updateTime":"2020-03-18T03:40:25.000Z","uid":55659,"like":8,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":22,"replies":[{"pid":"8cfe0f3723e2d1550af63bad2ee84f06864c74bd","tid":1929200,"uid":55659,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-16T21:40:06.000Z","msg":"<strong>San Francisco orders public not to leave home 'except for essential needs'</strong><br />\n<br />\nSan Francisco and surrounding counties totaling 6.7 million people will prohibit anyone from leaving their homes &quot;except for essential needs&quot; beginning at midnight Monday night.<br />\n<br />\nSan Francisco Mayor London Breed said at a news conference that the drastic steps are meant to slow the spread of the coronavirus.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The new public health order that we&rsquo;re announcing will require San Franciscans to remain at home with exceptions only for essential outings,&rdquo; she said. &ldquo;These measures will be disruptive to daily life, but there is no need to panic.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nIt's the largest city to impose an in-home curfew or other stay-home order in the United States so far. Similar orders will apply in several Bay Area counties until April 7, she said, though she added that date could change depending on the advice of health officials.<br />\n<br />\nPharmacies, grocery stores, banks, gas stations and essential government services will remain open, as will restaurants but for takeout and delivery orders only, Breed said. Bars and gyms will close. &ldquo;Your garbage will be picked up,&rdquo; she said.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nFailure to comply will be a misdemeanor offense, Police Chief Bill Scott said, but he and other officials said they&rsquo;re hoping for voluntary compliance.<br />\n<br />\nAd<br />\n<br />\nIt appeared to be the most extreme measure taken nationwide in response to the pandemic, and echoed similar steps taken in several European and Asian cities.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The virus is here in San Francisco. We must practice social distancing to slow it down,&rdquo; Dr. Grant Colfax, director of the city&rsquo;s Department of Public Health, said at the news conference.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Every hour counts,&rdquo; he said.<br />\n<br />\nWashington Gov. Jay Inslee, whose state has been at the center of the pandemic in the U.S., said Sunday he was planning to ban gatherings of more than 50 people, while Hoboken, New Jersey, announced a curfew on Saturday.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nIn Massachusetts, Gov. Charlie Baker said Sunday there were no plans for a shelter-in-place order there, despite other restrictions.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nColfax said health officials in several Bay Area counties spoke over the weekend and agreed that more radical action was necessary.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Today&rsquo;s decision was reached collectively, and the entire region is acting as one,&rdquo; he said.<br />\n<br />\nThe orders in the Bay Area will allow for some flexibility, officials said. People will be able to travel to shop for necessary supplies, access health care and provide aid to family and friends, as well as to exercise, the newspaper said.<br />\n<br />\nNorman Yee, president of the San Francisco Board of Supervisors, the city council, said other elected officials supported the mayor&rsquo;s action. He urged residents to comply.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;We can give orders, but if you don&rsquo;t follow it, they&rsquo;re useless,&rdquo; he said."},{"pid":"f24957dd0807090875dab0fb7a4f0b43878efc18","tid":1929200,"uid":55659,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-16T21:41:28.000Z","msg":"唔識打個藩字<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"fcf1a13e2083e39598f7601fdaf153c682fd8ac6","tid":1929200,"uid":41988,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-03-16T21:56:06.000Z","msg":"加拿大安省 今晚開始ban 洒巴 同 餐廳"},{"pid":"75c